This is for ALL my Eastern NC Trout ANGLERS!!! We are looking at a potential big change in our speckled trout fishery’s future.. new limits, new regulations on baits, season closures.. we need to let our voices be heard!! The speckled trout is one of the most beautiful inshore game fish our state has to offer!! Lets do whatever we can to keep our fisheries open, as well as healthy! Below, I’ve written a proposal that I think benefits everyone in the long run and helps us recreational trout anglers keep doing what we love so much! If anyone is looking to get involved PLEASE email: (MFC@NCDENR.GOV) label your email Speckled Trout Proposal when sending! This is an email address that will send your proposal directly to the Marine Fisheries Commission. If you agree with my proposal (listed below) please feel free to COPY and PASTE, or use pieces of it that you agree with and make your own proposal and sign off your name and send it in! We are trying to get as many people as we can to help overturn this new proposal they have issued! Below this post is my proposal, and if you agree or would like to make your own proposal PLEASE email the Marine Fisheries! I made it very easy to get involved all you have to do is copy and paste the email and send it!! Let’s all try our best to make a difference for our fisheries future! As a guide especially while my clients are fishing from kayaks, my number one priority before catching a single fish is to make sure my clients are as safe as they can possibly can be. I will not tolerate anybody purposely putting my clients in danger no matter what the reason.. especially if it’s a joke for your buddy’s to say “hey let’s wake out this kayaker”.. it’s one thing for an out of town guy that doesn’t know me or my business or what we are doing out there.. but for it to be locals let alone another guide out of the OBX, that can call me out by name and know damn well that those kayaks you just purposely waked out and then laughed loud enough for all of us to hear.. those are my clients.. it’s pathetic. Absolutely no common sense on the water, no etiquette, and no cares about the well being of my clients.. I’m not tagging the captain and edited the video so you can’t tell who it is because just as myself he’s trying to make a living off the water.. but if you listen to the video you can hear him joking that he already saw one of my clients struggling this morning as he unfortunately tipped his kayak while trying to land a fish within the first 30minutes of us being on the water.. he was perfect safe in shallow water, had a life jacket, and got right back in himself after a quick cool down.. but that being said and that captain already seeing how I had someone struggling instead of giving us some space he decided to drift into us and then trim his motor to purposely draw the biggest wake he could and we heard him and the two people onboard laughing about it as then pulled away.. so thats when I paddled over to confront them, and got this video.. the captains excuse was that he wasn’t the one driving the boat.. but he was right along laughing with his buddy’s and making fun of my client who just happened to have an accident and fall out, but instead of being decent human being decided hey let’s see if we can make him fall out again.. safety is priority on the water and always is.. I don’t care if my son is with me or not I’m not going to cuss you out or call you names but I will most definitely let you know if you put any of my clients in danger.
